                <h2>Goals and objectives</h2>
                <hr class="brief--hr">


                <p>



                    Defining the project goals is a crucial step in creating a successful whiteboard animation, regardless of whether it is created using recording equipment or special software tools. In order to effectively convey complex ideas and information, it is essential to have a clear understanding of what the animation should accomplish and who the intended audience is.
                    <br><br>
                    When creating a whiteboard animation using recording equipment, the project goals may be defined by the specific message that the business or organization wants to communicate. For example, the animation may be used to explain a new product or service, provide an overview of a complex process, or deliver a training message to employees. The use of recording equipment allows for a more customized and personalized approach to the animation, as the artist can create unique illustrations that are tailored to the specific needs of the project.
                    <br><br>
                    In contrast, when using special software tools to create a whiteboard animation, the project goals may be defined by the pre-made illustrations and animations that are available in the software library. While this approach may result in animations that are less unique and customized, it can be more cost-effective and efficient, as the illustrations and animations have already been created.
                    <br><br>
                    Regardless of the approach taken, it is important to be specific and clear about the desired outcome of the animation. This includes defining the intended audience, the message that the animation should convey, and any specific objectives that should be achieved through the animation. By defining the project goals in a clear and comprehensive manner, businesses and organizations can ensure that their whiteboard animation effectively communicates the desired message to the intended audience.

                </p>

                <p>Here are some examples of goals and objectives for a whiteboard animation:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Goal:</b> To explain the features and benefits of a new product to potential customers.</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Objectives:</li>
                        <li>a. To create an engaging and informative animation that highlights the key features of the product.</li>
                        <li>b. To communicate how the product can solve a specific problem or meet a specific need for potential customers.</li>
                        <li>c. To create a clear call-to-action that encourages viewers to take the next step in the sales process.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li><b>Goal:</b> To provide a visual overview of a complex process or system to employees.</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Objectives:</li>
                        <li>a. To create a clear and easy-to-follow animation that breaks down the process or system into manageable steps.</li>
                        <li>b. To communicate the importance of each step in the process or system, and how they fit together to achieve the desired outcome.</li>
                        <li>c. To ensure that employees have a clear understanding of the process or system, and feel confident in their ability to implement it effectively.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li><b>Goal:</b> To deliver a training message to employees on a specific topic.</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Objectives:</li>
                        <li>a. To create an engaging and informative animation that effectively communicates the training message.</li>
                        <li>b. To ensure that the animation is easy to follow and understand, and that key concepts are clearly presented.</li>
                        <li>c. To provide a clear call-to-action that encourages employees to apply what they have learned in their work.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li><b>Goal:</b> To promote a social cause or initiative to a wider audience.</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Objectives:</li>
                        <li>a. To create an emotional connection with the audience by using powerful storytelling and compelling visuals.</li>
                        <li>b. To clearly communicate the goals and objectives of the social cause or initiative, and why they are important.</li>
                        <li>c. To encourage viewers to take action and support the social cause or initiative in some way.</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>












